1. Avoid Unnecessary Re-renders (Core Optimization)
🧠 Problem
Every state/prop change triggers re-renders → wasted work

✅ Solution: Memoization
React.memo

const Child = React.memo(({ data }) => {
  return <div>{data}</div>;
});

👉 Prevents re-render if props don’t change

useMemo

const sorted = useMemo(() => heavySort(data), [data]);

👉 Avoid recomputing expensive values

useCallback

const handleClick = useCallback(() => {}, []);

👉 Prevents new function reference

⚠️ Trade-off
* Overuse = memory overhead + complexity



2. Code Splitting & Lazy Loading
🧠 Problem
Large JS bundle slows initial load

✅ Solution
Split code into chunks and load on demand

const Dashboard = React.lazy(() => import('./Dashboard'));


Deep Insight
* Splitting happens via dynamic import
* Lazy loading controls when it loads

⚠️ Trade-off
* Too many chunks → more network calls


3. Reduce Bundle Size
🧠 Problem
Large bundle = slow download + parse time

✅ Techniques
* Tree shaking
* Remove unused libs
* Import selectively

import debounce from 'lodash/debounce';



4. Optimize API Calls (Caching + Debounce)
🧠 Problem
Too many network calls + repeated fetching

✅ Solutions
Debounce

const debounced = debounce(fetchData, 300);

Caching
Use:
* React Query / SWR

🧠 Insight
👉 Network latency often > rendering cost



5.5. Virtualization (Large Lists)
